Stay Safe Online – Prevention Checklist (India)
As college students, being active online makes us more vulnerable to cyber threats. Follow these practical tips to stay safe:

✅ General Safety Tips
Use strong and unique passwords for all accounts (avoid using your name or birthdate).
Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) on email, social media, and banking apps.
Do not click on unknown links or download attachments from suspicious emails or messages.
Avoid using public Wi-Fi for logging into sensitive accounts like banking or college portals.
Keep your devices updated with the latest security patches and antivirus software.
Be careful about oversharing personal information on social media (phone number, address, college ID, etc.).
Verify job offers, scholarships, or internship links before applying—many scams target students.
Log out from accounts when using shared or public computers.
💳 Financial / UPI Safety Tips
Never share your UPI PIN, OTP, or bank details with anyone—even if they claim to be from the bank.
Do not accept unknown "collect requests" on UPI apps like Google Pay, PhonePe, or Paytm.
Always double-check the receiver’s name and UPI ID before sending money.
Avoid scanning QR codes from unknown or untrusted sources.
🚨 If You Become a Victim
Immediately report the incident on the National Cyber Crime Portal: https://cybercrime.gov.in
Call the Cyber Crime Helpline: 1930 for urgent financial fraud reporting.
Inform your bank as soon as possible to block suspicious transactions.
✔ Quick Reminder
Think before you click, verify before you trust, and act quickly if something feels suspicious.
